That's good to hear!
I'm actually trying to figure out how to add custom actions at all. The postman example on HubSpot's site has:
``` "actions": {
        "baseUrls": [
            "<https://www.example.com/HubSpot>"
        ]
    },```
But, to add a custom action, it seems like we need something like this:
```"actions": [
        {
          "type": "IFRAME",
          "width": 890,
          "height": 748,
          "uri": "<https://tools.hubteam.com/integrations-iframe-test-app>",
          "label": "Edit"
        },
        {
          "type": "CONFIRMATION_ACTION_HOOK",
          "confirmationMessage": "Are you sure you want to delete this ticket?",
          "confirmButtonText": "Yes",
          "cancelButtonText": "No",
          "httpMethod": "DELETE",
          "associatedObjectProperties": [
            "protected_account"
          ],
          "uri": "<https://api.hubapi.com/linked-sales-objects-test-application/v1/actions/demo-ticket/988>",
          "label": "Delete"
        }
      ]```
So I'm confused on how exactly to do that
